{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban MPs from accepting any gifts or donations from businesses and individuals",
        "additional_details": "Other public servants \u2014 such as police officers, doctors, or members of the armed forces \u2014 are not permitted to accept gifts which may be perceived to influence their professional decisions. We think the same standard must apply to politicians. We think that declaring a gift doesn\u2019t make it ethical, and that it\u2019s still a form of influence. We call for a complete ban on MPs accepting any gifts, payments, or hospitality from private individuals, companies, or lobbyists",
        "background": "Politicians are lawmakers and should be held to the highest standards of integrity. Yet MPs are currently allowed to accept gifts, hospitality, and donations from businesses and individuals. We think that even when declared, this can create a clear conflict of interest and undermine public trust.",
